Exxon Mobil, Boeing share losses lead Dow's 75-point fall

Behind losses for shares of Exxon Mobil and Boeing, the Dow Jones Industrial Average is declining Tuesday afternoon. The Dow DJIA, -1.68% was most recently trading 74 points (0.3%) lower, as shares of Exxon Mobil XOM, -2.23% and Boeing BA, -3.56% are contributing to the blue-chip gauge's intraday decline. Exxon Mobil's shares have fallen $1.32 (3.1%) while those of Boeing have dropped $3.71 (2.1%), combining for a roughly 35-point drag on the Dow. Also contributing significantly to the decline are Raytheon Technologies Corp. RTX, -0.28%, Pfizer PFE, -0.82%, and Chevron CVX, 0.31%. A $1 move in any one of the 30 components of the Dow results in a 6.86-point swing.

